OL,3,CHow Lebanon's volunteer medics risk
OL,4,Ctheir lives amid Israeli strikes
OL,6,FAdditional reporting by Content Editor
OL,7,FJessica Omari
OL,9,FTyre is once again under Israeli
OL,10,Fbombardment; we headed to the ancient
OL,11,Fcity in southern Lebanon to meet the
OL,12,Fbrave first responders working to save
OL,13,Fthe wounded.
OL,15,FThe seven men we met are all
OL,16,Fvolunteers; one, Shareef Hamadan, told
OL,17,Fus his wife cries every time he leaves
OL,18,Fthe house, fearing he won't return. He
OL,19,Fhas a two-month-old baby.
OL,21,FThose fears are not unfounded.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
